@baseUrl = http://localhost:5063

### ============================================================
### Authors
### ============================================================

### List all authors
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/authors?page=1&pageSize=10

### Search authors by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/authors?search=Orwell

### Get author by ID (George Orwell)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/authors/1

### Create a new author
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/authors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Gabriel",
  "lastName": "García Márquez",
  "biography": "Colombian novelist and Nobel Prize winner, author of 'One Hundred Years of Solitude'.",
  "birthDate": "1927-03-06",
  "country": "Colombia"
}

### Update an author
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/authors/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "George",
  "lastName": "Orwell",
  "biography": "English novelist, essayist, journalist, and critic. Best known for '1984' and 'Animal Farm'.",
  "birthDate": "1903-06-25",
  "country": "United Kingdom"
}

### Delete an author (will fail if author has books)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/authors/1

### ============================================================
### Categories
### ============================================================

### List all categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories?page=1&pageSize=10

### Get category by ID (Fiction - includes book count)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/1

### Create a new category
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Philosophy",
  "description": "Works exploring fundamental questions about existence, knowledge, and ethics"
}

### Update a category
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Fiction",
  "description": "Narrative literary works of imagination and creativity"
}

### Delete a category (will fail if category has books)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/1

### ============================================================
### Books
### ============================================================

### List all books
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?page=1&pageSize=10

### Search books by title
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?search=1984

### Search books by author name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?search=Asimov

### Filter books by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?category=Science Fiction

### Filter available books only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?available=true

### Filter unavailable books
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?available=false

### Sort books by title descending
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?sortBy=title&sortOrder=desc

### Get book by ID (1984 - includes authors, categories, availability)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/1

### Create a new book
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Road to Wigan Pier",
  "isbn": "978-0156767507",
  "publisher": "Harvest Books",
  "publicationYear": 1937,
  "description": "A study of working-class life in the industrial north of England.",
  "pageCount": 232,
  "language": "English",
  "totalCopies": 2,
  "authorIds": [1],
  "categoryIds": [3]
}

### Update a book
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/books/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "1984",
  "isbn": "978-0451524935",
  "publisher": "Signet Classics",
  "publicationYear": 1949,
  "description": "A dystopian masterpiece set in a totalitarian society under Big Brother's surveillance.",
  "pageCount": 328,
  "language": "English",
  "totalCopies": 4,
  "authorIds": [1],
  "categoryIds": [1, 6]
}

### Delete a book (will fail if book has active loans)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/books/2

### Get loan history for a book
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/1/loans?page=1&pageSize=10

### Get active reservations for a book
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/8/reservations?page=1&pageSize=10

### ============================================================
### Patrons
### ============================================================

### List all patrons
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?page=1&pageSize=10

### Search patrons by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?search=Alice

### Search patrons by email
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?search=bob.smith

### Filter patrons by membership type
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?membershipType=Premium

### Get patron by ID (includes active loans count and unpaid fines)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/1

### Create a new patron
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Grace",
  "lastName": "Hopper",
  "email": "grace.hopper@email.com",
  "phone": "555-0107",
  "address": "404 Tech Blvd",
  "membershipType": "Premium"
}

### Update a patron
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Bob",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "bob.smith@email.com",
  "phone": "555-0102",
  "address": "456 Elm St, Apt 2B",
  "membershipType": "Premium"
}

### Deactivate patron (will fail if patron has active loans)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/6

### Get patron's loans (filter by status)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/1/loans?status=active

### Get patron's reservations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/5/reservations

### Get patron's fines (filter by status)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/2/fines?status=unpaid

### ============================================================
### Loans
### ============================================================

### List all loans
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?page=1&pageSize=10

### Filter loans by status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?status=active

### Filter overdue loans
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?overdue=true

### Filter loans by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?fromDate=2026-01-01&toDate=2026-12-31

### Get loan details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/1

### Check out a book (standard checkout)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 7,
  "patronId": 5
}

### Return a book
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/1/return

### Renew a loan
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/3/renew

### Get all overdue loans (also flags overdue)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/overdue

### --- Business Rule Tests ---

### FAIL: Checkout when patron has too many unpaid fines (create a patron with high fines first)
### This tests the $10 fine threshold rule. Patron 4 has $1.00 in fines (under threshold).
### To test: manually add more fines to a patron, then try checkout.

### FAIL: Checkout for inactive patron (Patron 6 is inactive)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 2,
  "patronId": 6
}

### FAIL: Checkout when no copies available (Book 8 has 0 available)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 8,
  "patronId": 5
}

### FAIL: Renew an overdue loan (Loan 6 is overdue)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/6/renew

### FAIL: Renew a loan when there are pending reservations (Loan on book 1, reservation exists)
### Book 1 (1984) has a Ready reservation for patron 3
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/1/renew

### ============================================================
### Reservations
### ============================================================

### List all reservations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations?page=1&pageSize=10

### Filter reservations by status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations?status=pending

### Get reservation details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/1

### Create a reservation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 5,
  "patronId": 4
}

### Cancel a reservation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/1/cancel

### Fulfill a Ready reservation (Reservation 3 is Ready)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/3/fulfill

### FAIL: Reserve a book the patron already has on active loan
### Patron 1 has an active loan on Book 1 (1984)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 1,
  "patronId": 1
}

### ============================================================
### Fines
### ============================================================

### List all fines
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines?page=1&pageSize=10

### Filter unpaid fines
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines?status=unpaid

### Get fine details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines/1

### Pay a fine
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/fines/1/pay

### Waive a fine
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/fines/2/waive
